Joseph CODY et al., Appellants, v. DOSSIN’S FOOD PRODUCTS, Appellee. No. 10289. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. July 1, 1946. Edward T. Kelley, of Detroit, Mich., for appellant. Smith & Iiuffaker, of Detroit, Mich., for appellee.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The appeal in this case is dismissed for lack of diligence in prosecuting it.
